<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-10-14T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-10-14T08:00:00-05:00" n="625" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d625">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1428: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-10-14T09:00:00-04:00">October 14, 1931—9
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 1:15 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>104. My telegram No. 103, October 10, 2 p.m. The reply to the Legation’s
                            note presented pursuant to instructions to [<hi rend="italic">in</hi>]
                            the Department’s telegram No. 39, October 3, noon,<note n="96" xml:id="d625fn96">See footnote 86, <ref target="#pg_757">p.
                                    757</ref>.</note> states: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“In reply I am able to inform you that the delegation of Paraguay
                                    will be on the date indicated in Washington, properly instructed
                                    for the opening of the meetings”.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Wheeler</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>